

1.  Open Notepad:
2.  Write the code

3.  public class HelloWorld {
		    public static void main(String[] args) {
		        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
		    }
	}
4. Save the file: Save the file with a ".java" extension.

5. Open CMD

6. Navigate to the directory 

7. cd path\to\directory
8. Compile the Java file  : Use the javac command to compile the Java file.

9. javac HelloWorld.java

10 . Check for errors : If there are no errors, you'll see a new file named "HelloWorld.class" generated in the same directory.
11. Run the program: Use the java command to run the compiled Java program.

12. java HelloWorld
13. See the output: You should see the output "Hello, World!" printed in the CMD window.